commit.message: Adding High heat and Extreme heat alert categories
Rectifying temperature to celsius instead of fahrenheit
route doesn't have a .text. This was causing problems. Removing that call...it's not necessary anyways.
Adding Extreme Heat Alert
expecting route[0] instead of route now
Changing API to accept route object instead of maneuver object
Cancelling the backend routing call that was finding new routes instead of the same one used in the ui. This change should allow using the same route for both frontend and backend.
Removing fog conditions alert. It is too ambiguous to predict with this data. We have a Low Visibility alert already...so it should suffice for the moment.
Added many more hazards alerts.
Last piece of the getAllAlertsOnRoute integration
